author: Disney
description:
The original animated hit Lilo & Stitch has become a global franchise, spawning a 65-episode TV series, three direct-to-home entertainment films, a 26-episode anime series in Japan, multiple video games, theme park attractions, comics, books, a certified Platinum soundtrack album—and now, a live-action film inspired by the original. Chris Sanders (creator, writer, and original voice of Stitch), Maia Kealoha (Lilo in the new film), Tia Carrere (original voice of Nani, now playing Mrs. Kekoa), and Sydney Agudong (Nani in the live-action film) revisit the franchise’s enduring legacy and offer a closer look at the new movie. Moderated by Entertainment Tonight’s Denny Directo.
